[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "31:12-17 Orders were now given that a tabernacle should be set up for the service of God. But they must not think that the nature of the work, and the haste that was required, would justify them in working at it on sabbath days. The Hebrew word /shabath/ signifies rest, or ceasing from labour. The thing signified by the sabbath is that rest in glory which remains for the people of God; therefore the moral obligation of the sabbath must continue, till time is swallowed up in eternity.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 15:32-36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The distinction between the meaning of the two expressions, \"to be cut off from the people\", and \"to be put to death\", is here indicated. He who was cut off from the people had, by his offence, put himself out of the terms of the covenant, and was an outlaw. On such, and on such alone, when the offence was one which affected the well-being of the nation, as it was in this case, death could be inflicted by the public authority.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "12-17. Verily my sabbaths ye shall keep—The reason for the fresh inculcation of the fourth commandment at this particular period was, that the great ardor and eagerness, with which all classes betook themselves to the construction of the tabernacle, exposed them to the temptation of encroaching on the sanctity of the appointed day of rest. They might suppose that the erection of the tabernacle was a sacred work, and that it would be a high merit, an acceptable tribute, to prosecute the undertaking without the interruption of a day's repose; and therefore the caution here given, at the commencement of the undertaking, was a seasonable admonition.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "shall keep the sabbath",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " by observing or celebrating the sabbath, i. e. by observing or celebrating it, the antecedent being put for the relative, as is frequently done. So here is another most emphatical repetition to oblige us to the greater caution and diligence in this great duty, and to show what stress God lays upon it, who hath therefore placed this in the midst of the commands of the decalogue, as the heart which gives life and rigour to all the rest. Or it may be rendered thus; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall observe the day of rest to celebrate the sabbath",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and so the phrase is like that in the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "fourth command",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Remember the sabbath day to keep it holy. So here, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Observe the sabbath",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". i.e. watch its coming and approach, consider attentively the nature and use of it, and that not as a matter of idle speculation, but of serious practice; or, so that you may do or celebrate the sabbath, i.e. perform all the duties of it. Or thus, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall observe the sabbath, to make it a sabbath or day of rest",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and that no idle or carnal rest, but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a rest, holy to the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as it is called in the foregoing verse. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For a perpetual covenant",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or, by a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "perpetual covenant",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or, it is a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "perpetual covenant",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", i. e. condition or part of that agreement made between me and them. They have solemnly covenanted or promised that they will do all that I commanded them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Exodus 24:7,8",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 24:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",8",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", among which this is a chief branch; and I have covenanted to bless and sanctify them in so doing. And this word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "perpetual",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as also the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for ever",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", being added to it in the next verse, may intimate that this hath a longer perpetuity than the ceremonies, to which this phrase is sometimes ascribed, the rather because the reason of this perpetuity given in the next verse is such as hath its force not only till Christ, but even till the end of the world, and it is fit and just that men should retain this monument or memorial of the world’s creation even till its dissolution. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Wherefore the children of Israel shall keep the sabbath,.... On whom the sabbath of the seventh day was only enjoined, as well as that of the seventh and of the fiftieth years, being all ceremonial and shadowy: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to observe the sabbath throughout their generations; so long as the Mosaic dispensation lasted, and their civil polity and church state continued, even until the Messiah came, when all those Jewish shadows, rites, and ceremonies, fled away and disappeared: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for a perpetual covenant; just in the same sense as circumcision was, Genesis 17:13. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "for a perpetual covenant; just in the same sense as circumcision was, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 17:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
